assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: JFE Systems, Inc. provides information systems integration, operation, and maintenance services in Japan. The company provides systems integration services, including planning, designing, developing, operating, and maintenance of information systems. It also offers product-based solutions, such as building ERP, supply chain management systems, BI systems, cost management, procurement management systems, e-commerce, system coordination, digital form systems, and quality information management and method management systems for the food industry, as well as various packaged software solutions. In addition, the company provides infrastructure/cloud computing solutions, which includes cloud and server virtualization, information security support, emergency earthquake alert, voice-based cloud, LAN construction, and help desk services; office solutions, manufacturing site solutions, and platform development support services; systems development and maintenance in sales, production/logistics, accounting, costs, procurement, demand/supply, quality, accounts, annuities, and credit cards. It serves finance, food products, logistics, automotive, and other manufacturing industries. JFE Systems, Inc. was formerly known as Kawasaki Steel Systems R&D Corporation and changed its name to JFE Systems, Inc. in 2004. The company was incorporated in 1983 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan. JFE Systems, Inc. is a subsidiary of JFE Steel Corporation.
